Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua made a surprise visit to Kisii County where he is expected to popularise his Maendeleo Chap Chap Movement.Governor Mutua said his impromptu tour of the region was to test his movement s popularity ahead of a major political rally later this year. I am excited to come to Kisii. I am here to meet the common mwananchi in the streets, restaurants, supermarkets and tell them about Maendeleo Chap Chap Movement, he said. It is by meeting the people that you get to understand their thoughts and what they value most, he went on. The Governor, who earlier in the day attended the burial ceremony of former Cabinet minister William ole Ntimama in Narok County, also made a surprise stop at Nakumatt supermarket in the town to the amazement of many shoppers. He walked around the various isles picking various items and later on queued to pay at the counter. He also took selfies with shoppers. The Governor described corruption as a national cancer which needed to be tackled. email print email print Kenya is lobbying against the planned agreement between US and 12 Asian states for fear of losingPeres will be buried next to Rabin, who was assassinated in 1995 by a Jewish extremist opposed to